1
00:00:00,083 --> 00:00:01,450
(All characters, organizations,
and events in this drama are fictitious.)

2
00:00:01,450 --> 00:00:02,683
(Filming complied with guidelines
for children, youth, and animals.)

3
00:00:03,350 --> 00:00:05,083
Why are you doing this?

4
00:00:05,783 --> 00:00:08,050
He'll know who I am
if you say Lucky Joy Tech co-CEO.

5
00:00:08,050 --> 00:00:09,083
Lucky Joy!

6
00:00:09,683 --> 00:00:10,950
I just want to meet the CPO.

7
00:00:10,950 --> 00:00:12,150
- Why are you throwing me out?
- Lucky Joy?

8
00:00:33,250 --> 00:00:34,250
Do you...?

9
00:00:35,483 --> 00:00:36,550
Do you remember me?

10
00:00:37,750 --> 00:00:39,050
Thank you for helping me.

11
00:00:39,583 --> 00:00:41,083
Excuse me!

12
00:00:41,250 --> 00:00:42,250
Catch her!

13
00:00:44,050 --> 00:00:46,250
We told you to stop!

14
00:00:46,250 --> 00:00:48,683
I have something to discuss with the CPO!

15
00:00:49,650 --> 00:00:51,483
What's wrong with you people?

16
00:00:51,483 --> 00:00:52,683
- Gyeol.
- Why are you doing this?

17
00:00:52,850 --> 00:00:54,183
I just want to meet the CPO,

18
00:00:54,183 --> 00:00:55,683
- so why are you treating me like this?
- Hi, Seung Ri.

19
00:00:56,350 --> 00:00:57,383
Just a moment!

20
00:00:58,450 --> 00:01:00,050
- What are you doing?
- What's going on?

21
00:01:01,183 --> 00:01:02,850
I'm not sure either.

22
00:01:05,550 --> 00:01:07,383
If you're free, shall we grab some tea?

23
00:01:09,750 --> 00:01:10,750
- Shall we?
- Yeah.

24
00:01:18,950 --> 00:01:21,183
If you try to enter illegally again,

25
00:01:21,183 --> 00:01:22,383
we'll call the police.

26
00:01:27,250 --> 00:01:29,050
What kind of place is this?

27
00:01:29,250 --> 00:01:31,150
What is this, the NIS or the Blue House?

28
00:01:32,150 --> 00:01:33,150
Seriously.

29
00:01:35,050 --> 00:01:36,050
A girlfriend?

30
00:01:36,450 --> 00:01:38,350
That's impossible.

31
00:01:39,450 --> 00:01:42,283
What? Who threw water on whom?

32
00:01:43,283 --> 00:01:45,950
Hello? Mrs. Kang?

33
00:01:49,283 --> 00:01:51,650
Seo Seung Ri, how dare you?

34
00:01:54,650 --> 00:01:56,450
You're starting work next week?

35
00:01:56,450 --> 00:01:57,883
Yeah, that's how it turned out.

36
00:01:58,583 --> 00:02:00,083
I see.

37
00:02:00,083 --> 00:02:02,650
I thought you were just visiting
because of the Chairman.

38
00:02:02,650 --> 00:02:05,050
That was the plan at first...

39
00:02:05,883 --> 00:02:07,083
How about this?

40
00:02:08,650 --> 00:02:11,183
For now, accept the Chairman's proposal.

41
00:02:12,950 --> 00:02:14,650
The reason he made that proposal...

42
00:02:15,483 --> 00:02:17,550
is probably because he's worried
about the future of Kangsu Group.

43
00:02:18,550 --> 00:02:22,483
I'm sure he knows
that you're not really into management.

44
00:02:22,850 --> 00:02:24,050
If he knows that, then why...?

45
00:02:25,483 --> 00:02:26,650
Perhaps the Chairman felt that,

46
00:02:27,883 --> 00:02:29,150
for the future of Kangsu Group,

47
00:02:29,150 --> 00:02:30,950
a check was necessary.

48
00:02:31,483 --> 00:02:32,883
What kind of check?

49
00:02:33,250 --> 00:02:35,150
If you win the race,

50
00:02:35,150 --> 00:02:36,750
even without directly stepping
into management,

51
00:02:37,450 --> 00:02:40,450
you'll hold strong decision-making power
as the largest shareholder.

52
00:02:41,550 --> 00:02:44,150
You'll be a powerful force
that can prevent anyone's tyranny.

53
00:02:44,250 --> 00:02:46,450
There's no guarantee I'll win the race.

54
00:02:47,850 --> 00:02:48,883
Of course not.

55
00:02:49,550 --> 00:02:52,050
But perhaps he trusts your abilities,

56
00:02:52,950 --> 00:02:54,450
and by making him compete with you,

57
00:02:55,083 --> 00:02:57,650
he also wants to make Chief Ko stronger.

58
00:03:00,050 --> 00:03:01,983
You said you have a debt
to repay to the Chairman, right?

59
00:03:03,250 --> 00:03:04,350
It's painful to say,

60
00:03:05,483 --> 00:03:07,750
but the Chairman
doesn't have much time left.

61
00:03:10,150 --> 00:03:13,450
Think carefully
about what's best for the Chairman...

62
00:03:14,650 --> 00:03:15,850
and Kangsu Group.

63
00:03:18,850 --> 00:03:21,183
Okay, I'll think about it.

64
00:03:22,350 --> 00:03:24,950
So did you wrap everything up
in the U.S. and come back?

65
00:03:25,083 --> 00:03:27,150
Not wrapped up, just on pause.

66
00:03:27,650 --> 00:03:29,983
Coming back, I hadn't planned on working
at Kangsu Construction.

67
00:03:30,250 --> 00:03:33,150
- Which department?
- SP, Retirement Community Task Force.

68
00:03:33,383 --> 00:03:35,650
Really? That's the same department as me.

69
00:03:35,650 --> 00:03:37,350
Is it?

70
00:03:38,550 --> 00:03:39,950
How did you handle things...

71
00:03:39,950 --> 00:03:42,550
that the developer came all the way
to the company and caused a scene?

72
00:03:43,050 --> 00:03:45,383
What? I'm sorry, Chief.

73
00:03:45,950 --> 00:03:48,450
If that woman causes another scene,

74
00:03:48,750 --> 00:03:51,250
we'll seriously reconsider
bringing you on.

75
00:03:55,150 --> 00:03:57,450
Hey, what's going on?

76
00:03:58,550 --> 00:04:00,083
Do you know why Gyeol suddenly...

77
00:04:00,083 --> 00:04:01,950
decided to join the race?

78
00:04:02,350 --> 00:04:03,883
Maybe he got greedy.

79
00:04:03,883 --> 00:04:05,383
So, do you have a plan?

80
00:04:06,250 --> 00:04:07,883
Do you have a way to beat Gyeol?

81
00:04:08,450 --> 00:04:10,650
I'm the Chief Planning Officer
of Kangsu Construction.

82
00:04:11,483 --> 00:04:13,583
Do you think I can't beat
some complete rookie?

83
00:04:14,850 --> 00:04:17,450
Gyeol is a rising architect
the world is watching.

84
00:04:17,450 --> 00:04:19,250
He's not an easy opponent.

85
00:04:19,383 --> 00:04:20,383
I know that too.

86
00:04:20,950 --> 00:04:23,183
So please pay attention
to building the team.

87
00:04:23,950 --> 00:04:26,283
For design, we'll outsource
to the best design team...

88
00:04:26,283 --> 00:04:27,983
in the country. Just keep that in mind.

89
00:04:28,883 --> 00:04:30,383
Didn't you hear what your grandpa said?

90
00:04:30,783 --> 00:04:32,050
If I don't manage and supervise fairly,

91
00:04:32,050 --> 00:04:33,650
I'll be eliminated from the race!

92
00:04:33,950 --> 00:04:35,683
Then what, just sit back and lose?

93
00:04:44,083 --> 00:04:45,250
Let's go.

94
00:04:45,250 --> 00:04:46,850
I think I've taken too much
of your work time.

95
00:04:47,183 --> 00:04:48,183
Okay, Gyeol.

96
00:04:49,283 --> 00:04:50,983
Should I call you Team Leader now?

97
00:04:51,683 --> 00:04:52,983
The official appointment is next week.

98
00:04:57,383 --> 00:04:58,283
Mother.

99
00:04:58,650 --> 00:04:59,750
Hello, Ma'am.

100
00:04:59,950 --> 00:05:02,350
What, "Hello?" I ought to...

101
00:05:07,150 --> 00:05:08,183
Could you step aside for a moment?

102
00:05:13,650 --> 00:05:15,650
- You sit.
- Yes.

103
00:05:17,350 --> 00:05:19,050
Is something wrong, Mother?

104
00:05:19,183 --> 00:05:22,183
Didn't you hear? I said go your own way.

105
00:05:23,850 --> 00:05:24,850
Okay.

106
00:05:32,350 --> 00:05:33,383
Why are you doing this, Mother?

107
00:05:33,850 --> 00:05:36,750
Did you really throw water at Min Ho?

108
00:05:37,383 --> 00:05:39,983
Yes, I did. He deserved it.

109
00:05:39,983 --> 00:05:43,583
What? What did you say? He deserved it?

110
00:05:45,783 --> 00:05:48,550
Mother, I don't know what this is about,
but please don't do this here...

111
00:05:48,550 --> 00:05:49,983
Are you two-timing?

112
00:05:49,983 --> 00:05:52,750
Are you weighing your options
between Min Ho and Gyeol right now?

113
00:05:52,983 --> 00:05:53,983
Ma'am.

114
00:05:54,150 --> 00:05:55,950
There are many people watching.
Please stop.

115
00:05:56,383 --> 00:05:57,383
Let go!

116
00:05:58,650 --> 00:06:00,883
Answer me. Why did you follow him there?

117
00:06:01,750 --> 00:06:03,350
Why did you go
to someone else's blind date...

118
00:06:03,350 --> 00:06:05,150
and get in the way of Min Ho's future?

119
00:06:05,350 --> 00:06:06,850
I didn't follow him.

120
00:06:07,583 --> 00:06:09,983
Please get your facts straight
before speaking.

121
00:06:09,983 --> 00:06:11,450
My goodness.

122
00:06:13,050 --> 00:06:15,283
- Look at this insolence.
- Mother.

123
00:06:15,283 --> 00:06:18,683
I've held back all this time
for your parents' sake,

124
00:06:19,150 --> 00:06:20,283
but I won't tolerate it anymore.

125
00:06:21,050 --> 00:06:24,550
Watch your behavior, understand?

126
00:06:40,450 --> 00:06:41,450
Do you want to get some air?

127
00:06:42,883 --> 00:06:44,850
No, I should get back to work.

128
00:06:47,150 --> 00:06:48,583
I'm tougher than I look.

129
00:06:49,883 --> 00:06:53,050
I'm going to get an apology for today,
so don't worry too much.

130
00:06:57,783 --> 00:07:00,383
What? You threw water at Seung Ri?

131
00:07:00,383 --> 00:07:02,250
Yes, I did exactly...

132
00:07:02,250 --> 00:07:03,750
what she did to you.

133
00:07:03,750 --> 00:07:04,750
Mother.

134
00:07:05,050 --> 00:07:06,150
What a nasty woman.

135
00:07:06,450 --> 00:07:07,950
She didn't even blink...

136
00:07:07,950 --> 00:07:10,350
and told me to get my facts straight.

137
00:07:10,650 --> 00:07:14,250
Yes,
you should've gotten your facts straight.

138
00:07:14,850 --> 00:07:16,783
I did something
that deserved getting drenched.

139
00:07:16,783 --> 00:07:17,850
You...

140
00:07:17,850 --> 00:07:19,783
Enough! Have you all lost your minds?

141
00:07:19,783 --> 00:07:20,950
You startled me.

142
00:07:20,950 --> 00:07:22,183
Do you even realize what time it is?

143
00:07:23,183 --> 00:07:24,583
What do you mean? What time?

144
00:07:28,983 --> 00:07:29,983
Void the contract?

145
00:07:30,450 --> 00:07:32,583
It's a signed contract.
How is that possible?

146
00:07:33,283 --> 00:07:34,883
Theoretically, it's impossible.

147
00:07:35,550 --> 00:07:37,750
So I was planning to appeal to emotions,

148
00:07:38,183 --> 00:07:39,550
but that's been completely blocked.

149
00:07:39,750 --> 00:07:41,383
What do you mean? Explain it to me.

150
00:07:41,750 --> 00:07:44,883
"It's true that my seal is on it,
but I didn't stamp it myself.

151
00:07:44,883 --> 00:07:46,450
So the contract is invalid."

152
00:07:46,850 --> 00:07:49,083
I was going to try to appeal to them
on a personal level.

153
00:07:49,583 --> 00:07:51,250
Do you think that would work?

154
00:07:51,950 --> 00:07:52,983
It wouldn't, right?

155
00:07:53,483 --> 00:07:55,650
So I gave it some thought,

156
00:07:55,650 --> 00:07:57,683
- and I need to change my approach.
- How?

157
00:07:58,583 --> 00:08:00,850
A company's image is everything.

158
00:08:01,350 --> 00:08:02,683
To open the door for negotiation,

159
00:08:02,683 --> 00:08:04,550
I think I need to make some noise.

160
00:08:05,383 --> 00:08:06,383
Don't tell me...

161
00:08:06,483 --> 00:08:07,983
you're going to hold a demonstration,

162
00:08:07,983 --> 00:08:08,983
shouting "Step down" and "Down with them?"

163
00:08:11,183 --> 00:08:12,950
A demonstration? What demonstration?

164
00:08:14,150 --> 00:08:17,850
We're doing a demo day soon.

165
00:08:18,183 --> 00:08:19,183
Again?

166
00:08:19,583 --> 00:08:22,183
It worked last time
and secured investment.

167
00:08:22,483 --> 00:08:24,550
If we do it again and get more investment,
even better.

168
00:08:25,083 --> 00:08:26,083
I see.

169
00:08:26,750 --> 00:08:29,350
But is it okay to be relaxing like this
while working from home?

170
00:08:29,550 --> 00:08:30,850
Who's relaxing?

171
00:08:30,850 --> 00:08:32,850
We're having an idea meeting right now.

172
00:08:32,850 --> 00:08:33,850
That's right.

173
00:08:33,950 --> 00:08:35,650
I may not look it,

174
00:08:35,650 --> 00:08:38,850
but I'm a part-time special employee
at Lucky Joy.

175
00:08:38,850 --> 00:08:40,250
Sort of like an idea bank.

176
00:08:41,183 --> 00:08:42,250
Is that so?

177
00:08:43,650 --> 00:08:44,950
Come out and have lunch.

178
00:08:44,950 --> 00:08:46,950
Even remote workers should eat on time.

179
00:08:47,383 --> 00:08:49,783
I'll go eat with Grandma.

180
00:08:49,783 --> 00:08:51,150
I need to help prepare for the shop too.

181
00:08:51,483 --> 00:08:52,550
I'm going.

182
00:08:52,550 --> 00:08:53,950
Why not eat together?

183
00:08:56,050 --> 00:08:57,250
Bibimbap sounds good, right?

184
00:08:58,150 --> 00:09:00,483
I'm not really in the mood
to eat right now.

185
00:09:04,850 --> 00:09:07,650
No one's chasing you. Eat slowly.

186
00:09:08,450 --> 00:09:10,450
Your vegetable bibimbap is so good,

187
00:09:10,450 --> 00:09:12,250
it could bring
a runaway daughter-in-law back...

188
00:09:15,550 --> 00:09:16,750
At least it's a relief...

189
00:09:16,950 --> 00:09:19,250
that you're not starving yourself
over a breakup.

190
00:09:19,950 --> 00:09:22,050
I told you it's not a breakup.

191
00:09:28,550 --> 00:09:31,950
(Ji Hun)

192
00:09:34,950 --> 00:09:37,250
Wait, is that jerk a player?

193
00:09:38,150 --> 00:09:40,050
Going around with different women...

194
00:09:40,850 --> 00:09:41,883
Mom.

195
00:09:42,083 --> 00:09:44,350
Or did his family
oppose your relationship?

196
00:09:44,950 --> 00:09:46,650
Is his family that impressive?

197
00:09:47,050 --> 00:09:50,150
Please don't ever bring him up again.

198
00:09:50,583 --> 00:09:52,450
I'm completely over him.

199
00:09:56,550 --> 00:09:57,783
Do the dishes before you go upstairs.

200
00:09:59,550 --> 00:10:00,683
You don't have to tell me.

201
00:10:05,583 --> 00:10:06,683
All done.

202
00:10:07,350 --> 00:10:08,350
Hello.

203
00:10:08,550 --> 00:10:11,850
Hey. What's all done?

204
00:10:12,050 --> 00:10:15,250
It's a Kangsu Construction survey
targeting real estate agents.

205
00:10:16,050 --> 00:10:18,350
Do you get anything for doing that?

206
00:10:18,550 --> 00:10:20,183
They say there's a small gift.

207
00:10:21,650 --> 00:10:24,883
Well, nothing in this world
is free these days.

208
00:10:26,650 --> 00:10:29,050
Anyway, why is the office...

209
00:10:29,050 --> 00:10:32,550
so empty?

210
00:10:34,283 --> 00:10:36,083
There's not a single customer.

211
00:10:36,650 --> 00:10:38,350
It's like this all over the neighborhood.

212
00:10:38,950 --> 00:10:42,150
There's no development boom,
and the transportation isn't great either.

213
00:10:44,250 --> 00:10:45,283
More importantly,

214
00:10:46,150 --> 00:10:48,550
I'm thinking of quitting real estate.
What do you think?

215
00:10:49,250 --> 00:10:52,450
All of a sudden? Why quit?

216
00:10:52,950 --> 00:10:56,750
I want to travel the way I never could
when I was younger...

217
00:10:57,383 --> 00:10:59,450
and enjoy life a bit.

218
00:10:59,550 --> 00:11:00,750
Sure.

219
00:11:01,183 --> 00:11:03,783
The whole family is doing well,

220
00:11:03,783 --> 00:11:06,283
so there's no need to waste your life...

221
00:11:06,283 --> 00:11:08,950
in a cramped real estate office.

222
00:11:10,183 --> 00:11:13,783
The biggest regret people have
when they die...

223
00:11:14,350 --> 00:11:19,383
is not enjoying life
when they were younger.

224
00:11:19,750 --> 00:11:23,783
When you say it like that,
it makes me feel sorry toward you.

225
00:11:25,650 --> 00:11:29,450
Don't feel sorry for me.
We're not in the same situation.

226
00:11:30,250 --> 00:11:33,250
You have every right to enjoy life.

227
00:11:34,350 --> 00:11:36,150
Can I really do that?

228
00:11:36,150 --> 00:11:37,550
Of course.

229
00:11:38,450 --> 00:11:41,783
As you get older,
your children become your status.

230
00:11:42,550 --> 00:11:43,683
A professor, a doctor,

231
00:11:43,683 --> 00:11:46,383
and even a daughter who's a company CEO.

232
00:11:47,750 --> 00:11:51,050
They're the top of the top.
You have every right to enjoy life.

233
00:11:59,650 --> 00:12:02,150
What? Make them compete with Gyeol?

234
00:12:02,750 --> 00:12:04,450
This is like handing it over
on a silver platter.

235
00:12:05,550 --> 00:12:08,350
Maid, give me some cold water.

236
00:12:10,550 --> 00:12:11,550
Where's the maid?

237
00:12:12,450 --> 00:12:13,450
Out grocery shopping.

238
00:12:13,650 --> 00:12:16,450
What is it?
Did something frustrating happen again?

239
00:12:18,450 --> 00:12:20,450
It's fine, I'll do it myself.

240
00:12:23,183 --> 00:12:24,350
Stay on Mother's good side.

241
00:12:24,883 --> 00:12:27,783
There's nothing to gain
from upsetting her.

242
00:12:29,750 --> 00:12:32,483
She's going to give away
the remaining 20 percent?

243
00:12:33,350 --> 00:12:34,350
That's ridiculous.

244
00:12:36,783 --> 00:12:38,050
Are you preparing kimchi or something?

245
00:12:38,550 --> 00:12:40,150
Why so much ginger?

246
00:12:40,550 --> 00:12:43,383
I'm going to make ginger pancakes.
What about lunch?

247
00:12:45,050 --> 00:12:48,250
I'll take care of it myself.
Have you eaten, Mother?

248
00:12:49,950 --> 00:12:51,183
You're all here.

249
00:12:53,950 --> 00:12:55,283
What's all this? You didn't have to.

250
00:12:55,950 --> 00:12:58,383
I thought the Chairman
would need soft food,

251
00:12:58,783 --> 00:12:59,950
so I made some steamed sea bream.

252
00:13:00,450 --> 00:13:03,783
If you have time for that,
keep your daughter in line instead.

253
00:13:04,650 --> 00:13:06,650
What? What do you mean?

254
00:13:06,650 --> 00:13:07,650
I told you, didn't I?

255
00:13:08,150 --> 00:13:10,783
Don't even dream of reaching...

256
00:13:10,783 --> 00:13:12,750
for something out of your league.

257
00:13:13,350 --> 00:13:14,550
Not knowing her place,

258
00:13:14,550 --> 00:13:16,550
she followed Min Ho to his blind date...

259
00:13:16,750 --> 00:13:19,950
What? Seung Ri went where?

260
00:13:19,950 --> 00:13:21,950
Not only did she follow him,

261
00:13:22,350 --> 00:13:23,950
but she also threw water at Min Ho.

262
00:13:24,750 --> 00:13:26,583
How did you raise your daughter?

263
00:13:26,950 --> 00:13:28,750
What's wrong with you? Stop it.

264
00:13:28,750 --> 00:13:30,083
I just got back...

265
00:13:30,083 --> 00:13:32,450
after returning the favor to Seung Ri.

266
00:13:32,750 --> 00:13:38,450
Wait, so you threw water at my Seung Ri?

267
00:13:38,583 --> 00:13:42,250
Yes. Poke me with a needle,
I'll come back with a sword.

268
00:13:42,850 --> 00:13:44,450
Be thankful she didn't get slapped.

269
00:13:46,483 --> 00:13:48,350
I don't know the full details,

270
00:13:49,250 --> 00:13:51,650
but Seung Ri wouldn't have gone there
on her own.

271
00:13:52,550 --> 00:13:54,450
If you returned it with words, then I...

272
00:13:55,483 --> 00:13:58,350
will return it tenfold. Keep that in mind!

273
00:13:58,983 --> 00:13:59,983
Got it?

274
00:14:05,583 --> 00:14:07,183
What?

275
00:14:07,950 --> 00:14:10,683
If you have something to say, say it.
Don't just glare.

276
00:14:13,250 --> 00:14:15,650
Calm down and go sit over there.

277
00:14:15,650 --> 00:14:18,083
I'll make some tea, Jeong Ran.

278
00:14:18,350 --> 00:14:22,550
I'm sorry, Madam. I'll take my leave now.

279
00:14:29,050 --> 00:14:31,783
Just as Min Ho is a precious son to you,

280
00:14:33,250 --> 00:14:37,750
Seung Ri is a precious daughter to me.

281
00:14:38,283 --> 00:14:39,283
So what?

282
00:14:39,850 --> 00:14:42,350
That's all I'm saying.

283
00:14:46,983 --> 00:14:49,050
Did anyone say she wasn't precious?

284
00:14:49,650 --> 00:14:50,650
So why...?

285
00:14:50,650 --> 00:14:52,250
What's wrong with you, really?

286
00:15:09,083 --> 00:15:10,250
I trust my daughter.

287
00:15:10,683 --> 00:15:12,483
You must've had a reason to throw water.

288
00:15:12,483 --> 00:15:14,650
What are you talking about? Throw water?

289
00:15:14,650 --> 00:15:15,983
It's nothing, Dad.

290
00:15:16,750 --> 00:15:18,283
Tell me what happened.

291
00:15:18,283 --> 00:15:20,650
I went to the Chairman's house today...

292
00:15:20,650 --> 00:15:22,450
I had a bit of an issue with Chief Ko.

293
00:15:22,450 --> 00:15:24,550
It's nothing serious, so don't worry.

294
00:15:24,550 --> 00:15:27,150
It is serious. Is only her son important?

295
00:15:27,150 --> 00:15:28,250
My daughter is important...

296
00:15:28,250 --> 00:15:30,250
Don't get involved in the kids' affairs
without any dignity...

297
00:15:30,250 --> 00:15:31,950
Doesn't it upset you?

298
00:15:32,250 --> 00:15:34,650
Stop it, Mom. I went too far too.

299
00:15:35,083 --> 00:15:37,050
And I'll make sure I get an apology.

300
00:15:37,750 --> 00:15:39,783
Really? You'd better.

301
00:15:40,183 --> 00:15:42,950
Otherwise,
I'll be too upset to live with it.

302
00:15:44,083 --> 00:15:45,550
Why did you stop eating?

303
00:15:45,850 --> 00:15:47,450
I made expensive steamed sea bream
for once.

304
00:15:48,583 --> 00:15:49,650
I'm done.

305
00:15:52,250 --> 00:15:54,750
I'll get up too. Thank you for the meal.

306
00:15:56,883 --> 00:15:58,050
This is really upsetting.

307
00:16:00,150 --> 00:16:01,550
It's hot.

308
00:16:02,450 --> 00:16:04,150
- Steamed sea bream!
- It's hot.

309
00:16:04,150 --> 00:16:05,483
It's hot.

310
00:16:05,483 --> 00:16:07,983
I see that you sent another gift
to the Chairman's family again.

311
00:16:08,450 --> 00:16:09,550
What did you say?

312
00:16:11,650 --> 00:16:13,283
And you,
wearing your sister's clothes again?

313
00:16:14,183 --> 00:16:16,083
- I told you not to wear her clothes!
- Wait...

314
00:16:16,083 --> 00:16:17,050
Did I or didn't I?

315
00:16:17,050 --> 00:16:18,050
Geez...

316
00:16:18,483 --> 00:16:20,750
You make my life so hard, seriously.

317
00:16:20,750 --> 00:16:22,250
Don't touch me.

318
00:16:22,250 --> 00:16:24,050
You know how your sister gets!

319
00:16:38,583 --> 00:16:40,750
(Kangsu Construction HQ,
Day Shift Team One)

320
00:16:48,650 --> 00:16:50,150
Hello, it's me.

321
00:16:50,850 --> 00:16:53,250
I have a bit of a situation,

322
00:16:54,150 --> 00:16:56,050
so I don't think I can take
the Kangsu Construction assignment.

323
00:16:56,950 --> 00:16:58,683
Could you switch my area?

324
00:16:58,983 --> 00:17:01,050
Are you saying you want
to pick and choose?

325
00:17:01,383 --> 00:17:02,383
Then quit.

326
00:17:02,883 --> 00:17:04,650
There are plenty
of others willing to do it.

327
00:17:05,550 --> 00:17:07,650
Hello?

328
00:17:11,050 --> 00:17:12,783
- This is nuts.
- Honey.

329
00:17:12,783 --> 00:17:15,750
Cho Eun Ae, Dr. Cho,
everyone, come out here.

330
00:17:18,750 --> 00:17:20,983
- Why? What's going on?
- You called, Mom?

331
00:17:21,450 --> 00:17:23,850
Sit down, all of you. What do you think?

332
00:17:24,350 --> 00:17:27,850
A Western Europe package.
France, Italy, Switzerland.

333
00:17:30,850 --> 00:17:32,950
Your 60th birthday is coming up.

334
00:17:32,950 --> 00:17:35,550
Let's go on a trip to Europe then.

335
00:17:36,650 --> 00:17:38,550
Right, Dad's turning 60 soon.

336
00:17:39,550 --> 00:17:42,250
Dad still looks so young,
but he's already 60?

337
00:17:42,550 --> 00:17:46,250
You should plan something like that
gradually over time,

338
00:17:46,550 --> 00:17:47,550
not suddenly like this.

339
00:17:48,450 --> 00:17:50,250
What do you mean suddenly?

340
00:17:50,483 --> 00:17:53,083
I've been talking about traveling...

341
00:17:53,083 --> 00:17:55,550
to Europe for your 60th for 10 years.

342
00:17:56,583 --> 00:17:58,583
You can take about ten days off, right?

343
00:17:59,783 --> 00:18:00,850
Days off?

344
00:18:00,850 --> 00:18:03,883
You didn't take your summer vacation
and worked all through it.

345
00:18:03,883 --> 00:18:06,950
If you combine that, you should be able
to take ten days, right?

346
00:18:07,750 --> 00:18:09,850
I can't take ten days off.

347
00:18:09,850 --> 00:18:12,950
Things at work don't go as I want.

348
00:18:13,283 --> 00:18:15,650
You're an executive at a major company.

349
00:18:16,450 --> 00:18:17,583
You have all your legal holidays.

350
00:18:17,583 --> 00:18:20,450
How have you not taken a single vacation
since last year?

351
00:18:20,750 --> 00:18:23,383
She's right, Dad.
Go on the trip this time.

352
00:18:23,883 --> 00:18:25,983
You've been too tied up with work.

353
00:18:27,383 --> 00:18:29,550
I'll check my schedule at work first.

354
00:18:29,550 --> 00:18:31,450
Don't say you can't.

355
00:18:31,983 --> 00:18:34,150
You've raised your children well,

356
00:18:34,150 --> 00:18:36,750
and you've faithfully provided
for this family all this time.

357
00:18:37,150 --> 00:18:39,950
You deserve to enjoy that much. Right?

358
00:18:40,250 --> 00:18:43,050
Of course you do.

359
00:18:43,050 --> 00:18:47,883
And don't worry
about how much you should contribute.

360
00:18:47,883 --> 00:18:49,250
I know your situations well.

361
00:18:49,683 --> 00:18:51,850
Hasn't your situation improved, Eun Ae?

362
00:18:51,983 --> 00:18:53,550
You even received an investment
from a major company.

363
00:18:53,750 --> 00:18:56,450
Well, yeah.

364
00:18:56,750 --> 00:18:57,750
It's fine.

365
00:18:59,650 --> 00:19:00,650
Look.

366
00:19:01,083 --> 00:19:04,850
This is the savings account I've built
for a trip over ten years.

367
00:19:07,550 --> 00:19:09,850
You saved this for ten years?

368
00:19:10,850 --> 00:19:14,083
Mom, you really had a plan all along.

369
00:19:15,750 --> 00:19:17,183
How much is it?

370
00:19:17,583 --> 00:19:20,083
One, two, three, four zeroes...

371
00:19:20,083 --> 00:19:21,083
You saved 10,000 dollars?

372
00:19:24,250 --> 00:19:26,050
Why make a face pack at home?

373
00:19:26,550 --> 00:19:28,550
There are so many good ones these days.

374
00:19:28,550 --> 00:19:32,350
Those can't compare
to handmade natural packs by me.

375
00:19:33,050 --> 00:19:35,750
Dad, will this make me prettier?

376
00:19:35,950 --> 00:19:36,950
Of course.

377
00:19:37,383 --> 00:19:39,150
Mom needs it to keep her skin hydrated...

378
00:19:39,150 --> 00:19:40,583
because airplane cabins are so dry.

379
00:19:41,150 --> 00:19:43,350
You're already pretty, Bit Na,

380
00:19:43,583 --> 00:19:44,950
but this will make you even prettier.

381
00:19:46,450 --> 00:19:48,250
Why do you have a bandage on your finger?

382
00:19:49,483 --> 00:19:50,583
I put some ointment on it.

383
00:19:52,750 --> 00:19:54,183
I'm sleepy.

384
00:19:54,183 --> 00:19:55,583
Bit Na, go to sleep if you're tired.

385
00:19:55,950 --> 00:19:58,450
I'll take the pack off later
and carry you to your room.

386
00:20:03,550 --> 00:20:04,550
Hey, Eun Nim.

387
00:20:06,183 --> 00:20:08,850
What? A trip to Europe?

388
00:20:12,650 --> 00:20:15,650
Okay, let's get together soon and plan it.

389
00:20:17,883 --> 00:20:18,950
Who was that?

390
00:20:19,083 --> 00:20:20,550
It was Eun Nim.

391
00:20:21,150 --> 00:20:24,150
Mom and Dad are going to Europe
for Dad's 60th birthday.

392
00:20:24,850 --> 00:20:26,150
Who celebrates 60 like that these days?

393
00:20:26,450 --> 00:20:29,450
It's more like a turning point in life
than just a number.

394
00:20:31,183 --> 00:20:34,483
So if we could contribute
to their travel expenses...

395
00:20:35,250 --> 00:20:36,250
What?

396
00:20:37,683 --> 00:20:38,683
Travel expenses?

397
00:20:39,183 --> 00:20:40,550
You have to leave it on
for ten more minutes.

398
00:20:41,050 --> 00:20:42,283
The face pack isn't the issue right now.

399
00:20:42,650 --> 00:20:44,450
Who's paying for the travel expenses?

400
00:20:44,750 --> 00:20:47,350
Mom said she's been saving for it,

401
00:20:47,350 --> 00:20:50,650
so we shouldn't worry.
How can we just leave it at that?

402
00:20:51,483 --> 00:20:54,050
As the eldest son,
I should at least contribute something.

403
00:20:54,050 --> 00:20:56,083
With what money?

404
00:20:56,750 --> 00:20:57,950
Think about it, honey.

405
00:20:58,883 --> 00:21:02,150
Among my siblings, I've received
the most financial support from them.

406
00:21:02,483 --> 00:21:05,150
And they take care of Bit Na too.

407
00:21:05,583 --> 00:21:07,050
Of course I want to help too,

408
00:21:07,450 --> 00:21:09,250
but are we really in a position to?

409
00:21:10,650 --> 00:21:12,683
I'll think more about the travel expenses.

410
00:21:13,683 --> 00:21:15,750
Go ahead and sleep.
I still have some lecture prep to do.

411
00:21:16,883 --> 00:21:17,883
Good night.

412
00:21:28,483 --> 00:21:30,850
What? You're leaving for work already?

413
00:21:31,950 --> 00:21:33,250
It's not even 5 a.m.

414
00:21:34,283 --> 00:21:37,083
I signed up for a pool near the office.

415
00:21:38,250 --> 00:21:40,050
I think I've been gaining weight.

416
00:21:40,050 --> 00:21:42,050
I'll work out
and go straight to work from there.

417
00:21:42,283 --> 00:21:43,283
Swimming?

418
00:21:44,150 --> 00:21:45,750
You can't go out on an empty stomach.

419
00:21:45,750 --> 00:21:47,350
At least eat something.

420
00:21:47,550 --> 00:21:50,150
No, I'll just eat something
after working out.

421
00:21:50,383 --> 00:21:51,950
Get some more sleep.

422
00:21:52,350 --> 00:21:54,950
Starting tomorrow,
I'll prepare something simple beforehand.

423
00:21:55,083 --> 00:21:56,450
Make sure you eat breakfast.

424
00:21:56,450 --> 00:21:57,450
Okay.

425
00:22:04,550 --> 00:22:05,850
That's a relief.

426
00:22:06,450 --> 00:22:08,750
Gyeol accepted your decision so readily.

427
00:22:09,850 --> 00:22:12,050
He hasn't fully accepted it yet.

428
00:22:13,950 --> 00:22:17,450
I hope Min Ho and his father...

429
00:22:18,750 --> 00:22:20,683
also understand my intentions
and do their part.

430
00:22:21,450 --> 00:22:24,583
Stop worrying about the children.

431
00:22:25,183 --> 00:22:26,950
Who's worrying about whom?

432
00:22:28,650 --> 00:22:32,750
Now it's your turn, Mrs. Lee Yeong Hwa.

433
00:22:34,283 --> 00:22:37,550
How about we grant each other...

434
00:22:37,550 --> 00:22:39,350
one wish a day?

435
00:22:39,750 --> 00:22:41,083
Grant a wish?

436
00:22:44,550 --> 00:22:45,550
Where's Gyeol?

437
00:22:46,483 --> 00:22:48,650
He already left for work.

438
00:22:50,050 --> 00:22:52,250
He could've gone with me.
He doesn't even have a car.

439
00:22:57,283 --> 00:22:58,683
The car is ready, sir.

440
00:22:58,850 --> 00:23:01,550
Why come here
instead of going straight to the company?

441
00:23:01,783 --> 00:23:04,150
I have something to report privately
in the car. Let's go.

442
00:23:05,350 --> 00:23:06,950
- I'll be back.
- Yes.

443
00:23:11,150 --> 00:23:12,283
Let's go, sir.

444
00:23:12,683 --> 00:23:13,683
Mr. Ju.

445
00:23:14,183 --> 00:23:16,283
Do you have anything important...

446
00:23:16,283 --> 00:23:18,583
to report to me in the car?

447
00:23:19,850 --> 00:23:20,883
Pardon?

448
00:23:20,883 --> 00:23:24,350
I feel like I gave you
an important instruction recently.

449
00:23:26,750 --> 00:23:28,883
Spying on the Chairman's office...

450
00:23:28,883 --> 00:23:30,250
Just go.

451
00:23:30,250 --> 00:23:31,250
I said go. Get out.

452
00:23:32,583 --> 00:23:33,650
Go.

453
00:23:33,650 --> 00:23:34,750
Mother, I'll see you later.

454
00:23:38,483 --> 00:23:41,183
Maid, make me an espresso...

455
00:23:44,250 --> 00:23:46,750
Nevermind. I'll make it myself.

456
00:23:48,583 --> 00:23:52,450
Kangsu Construction, wake up!

457
00:23:52,650 --> 00:23:55,950
Give me back Joy!

458
00:23:56,150 --> 00:23:59,450
It started and stopped!

459
00:24:01,483 --> 00:24:02,550
Seriously.

460
00:24:06,050 --> 00:24:07,983
Kangsu Construction, wake up!

461
00:24:07,983 --> 00:24:11,150
Give me back Joy!

462
00:24:11,783 --> 00:24:12,850
Hey, catch her!

463
00:24:15,350 --> 00:24:16,450
Get her!

464
00:24:19,750 --> 00:24:22,750
Remember this.
Kangsu Retirement Community...

465
00:24:23,150 --> 00:24:27,250
was not just my dream,
but your father's too.

466
00:24:27,983 --> 00:24:29,783
Yes, I understand.

467
00:24:30,450 --> 00:24:33,083
Now that you've joined the company,

468
00:24:34,550 --> 00:24:37,483
I can finally set my mind at ease
and take some time for myself.

469
00:24:37,883 --> 00:24:39,383
Your time, Grandpa?

470
00:24:39,950 --> 00:24:44,650
I've missed too much while carrying
Kangsu Construction on my shoulders.

471
00:24:49,050 --> 00:24:50,250
I'm sorry, Grandpa.

472
00:24:52,150 --> 00:24:53,150
Hello?

473
00:24:53,750 --> 00:24:56,183
To the CPO's office? Yes, understood.

474
00:24:57,583 --> 00:24:59,350
- Is it Chief Ko?
- Yes.

475
00:25:01,183 --> 00:25:02,683
Learn well from him,

476
00:25:03,350 --> 00:25:06,083
and compete well together.

477
00:25:06,350 --> 00:25:08,450
Yes, I'll be going now.

478
00:25:29,050 --> 00:25:30,050
Looks like...

479
00:25:31,850 --> 00:25:34,750
it's almost time for me
to leave this place as well.

480
00:25:45,283 --> 00:25:47,283
(Chairman)

481
00:25:48,650 --> 00:25:49,650
I wonder...

482
00:25:51,483 --> 00:25:54,450
how many times
will I be able to come here.

483
00:25:58,250 --> 00:26:02,550
Kangsu Construction, wake up!

484
00:26:05,983 --> 00:26:07,583
I need to use the restroom.
What should I do?

485
00:26:08,850 --> 00:26:10,083
(Kangsu Construction)

486
00:26:12,450 --> 00:26:13,450
Right.

487
00:26:22,450 --> 00:26:23,883
We scan from here to here,

488
00:26:24,350 --> 00:26:27,350
and then from that end like this.

489
00:26:33,950 --> 00:26:34,983
I don't know.

490
00:26:47,083 --> 00:26:49,650
I'm protesting, but there's no reaction.

491
00:26:50,183 --> 00:26:52,683
Why isn't that CPO even budging?

492
00:27:00,350 --> 00:27:04,050
Excuse me, is the cleaning lady inside?

493
00:27:05,183 --> 00:27:06,183
Excuse me.

494
00:27:06,350 --> 00:27:07,783
(Head of Division's Office)

495
00:27:11,683 --> 00:27:14,450
I'm sorry. I'll clean it up right away.

496
00:27:19,050 --> 00:27:20,350
Why is Dad here?

497
00:27:25,483 --> 00:27:27,150
What did he just do to my dad?

498
00:27:29,850 --> 00:27:31,350
Hey, you jerk!

499
00:27:52,283 --> 00:27:54,850
(Our Happy Days)

500
00:27:55,050 --> 00:27:56,350
I'm not a suspicious person.

501
00:27:56,350 --> 00:27:58,883
I'm the developer
of the program your company acquired!

502
00:27:59,050 --> 00:28:01,083
Are you Cho Seong Jun?

503
00:28:02,350 --> 00:28:04,883
The top student from school
is now a janitor?

504
00:28:05,550 --> 00:28:06,950
- Apologize to Seung Ri.
- Hey, no!

505
00:28:06,950 --> 00:28:09,983
If you don't apologize,
I'll keep punishing myself.

506
00:28:09,983 --> 00:28:10,983
Are you crazy?

507
00:28:10,983 --> 00:28:13,450
It seems you're finally ready to talk.

508
00:28:13,950 --> 00:28:14,983
Shall we begin?

509
00:28:15,050 --> 00:28:16,750
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
